e pilgrims must fulfill the following eligibility criteria to fill the application form:-All the Pilgrims must be an Indian Citizen.Subsequently, candidates must possess an Indian Passport having remaining validity of at-least 6 months as on 1 September of that year.The candidates should belong to the age group of 18 years to 70 years on 1 January of the current financial year.The Body Mass Index (BMI) of all the pilgrims must lie below 25.All the pilgrims must be physically fit for travelling.Furthermore, foreign nationals are not eligible to apply and thus excludes OCI Cardholders.For more details on the Eligibility Criteria \u2013 Click HereFees and ExpenditureThe pilgrims have to pay the fees for travelling to the Kailash Mansarovar Yatra. Subsequently, pilgrims can see the details of Fees using the link given below:- Fees & ExpenditureSelection ProcedureMinistry of External Affairs will select all the pilgrims through computerized process. For more details, please click the link given below:- Selection ProcedureNeed for Medical CheckupFor Kailash Mansarover Yatra 2018, pilgrims have to climb up to 19,500 feet in worst weather conditions. This Mansarovar Yatra is risky so all the pilgrims must be physically fit & needs to clear health check-up.Delhi govt. will manage the food and lodging facility for such passengers during their stay in Delhi (3 to 4 days) before journey. However, people who have already performed their health checkups through DHLI and ITBP need not clear this health check up again.Routes Map & Details of Kailash Mansarovar Yatra 2018Candidates can take any one of the 2 routes to travel to Kailash Mansarovar:-Route 1Lipulekh Pass (Uttarakhand)Route Map18 Batons24 days Travel PeriodRs. 1.6 lakh Expenditure (per batch)DetailsRoute 2Nathu La (Sikkim)Route Map8 Batons21 days Travel PeriodAround 2 Million bucks Expenditure (per batch)DetailsReferences\u2014 For any further information, candidates can see FAQ\u2019s using the link given below:- FAQ\u2